---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro'
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Where Does Your Business Fit? — Upstate Web Co"
  description="Three paths to a web presence: DIY AI builders, full-service agencies, or custom-built by UWC. See the real costs, tradeoffs, and what you actually own."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FBF8F4] py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#1A1814] leading-tight">
        Where does your business fit?
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[#1A1814]/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        There are three ways to get a website today. Each has tradeoffs. Here's an honest look at all three — so you can decide what's right for your business.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three Lanes -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <!-- Lane 1: DIY AI Builders -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[#E8E4DE] p-6">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🤖</div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1A1814]">DIY AI Builders</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#1A1814]/60 mt-1 mb-4">Wix, Squarespace, Durable, B12, GoDaddy Airo</p>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Good for:</p>
            <p class="text-[#1A1814]/70">"I just need something up." Fast, cheap, handles the basics.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Cost:</p>
            <p class="text-[#1A1814]/70">$10-50/month forever. You never stop paying.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-green-700">Pros:</p>
            <ul class="text-[#1A1814]/70 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Live in minutes</li>
              <li>No technical skills needed</li>
              <li>Low monthly cost to start</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-red-700">Tradeoffs:</p>
            <ul class="text-[#1A1814]/70 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Looks like every other site on the platform</li>
              <li>Slow load times (4-8+ seconds)</li>
              <li>Can't add custom features (booking rules, AI chat)</li>
              <li>You never own the code — locked to the platform</li>
              <li>Wix sites get 1.4% organic traffic rate</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Lane 2: Full-Service Agencies -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[#E8E4DE] p-6">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🏢</div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1A1814]">Full-Service Agencies</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#1A1814]/60 mt-1 mb-4">Local WordPress shops, Hibu, UENI</p>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Good for:</p>
            <p class="text-[#1A1814]/70">Businesses with big budgets that want a full marketing team.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Cost:</p>
            <p class="text-[#1A1814]/70">$3,000-$25,000+ for the build. $200-$7,000/month ongoing.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-green-700">Pros:</p>
            <ul class="text-[#1A1814]/70 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>More customization than templates</li>
              <li>Someone else manages everything</li>
              <li>Bundled marketing services</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-red-700">Tradeoffs:</p>
            <ul class="text-[#1A1814]/70 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Expensive — overkill for most solopreneurs</li>
              <li>8-16 week timelines</li>
              <li>Often locked into proprietary CMS</li>
              <li>WordPress sites slow down as plugins pile up</li>
              <li>Some agencies hold your domain hostage</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Lane 3: UWC -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-[#B85C38] p-6 bg-[#FBF8F4]/50">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">⚡</div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1A1814]">Custom-Built by UWC</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#B85C38] mt-1 mb-4">One-time build. You own everything.</p>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Good for:</p>
            <p class="text-[#1A1814]/70">Businesses that outgrew templates — or are smart enough to skip that step.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Cost:</p>
            <p class="text-[#1A1814]/70">$750-$3,500 one-time. Optional retainer. No platform fees.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-green-700">You get:</p>
            <ul class="text-[#1A1814]/70 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Custom design — looks like your business, not a template</li>
              <li>95+ Google PageSpeed (fast = better ranking)</li>
              <li>AI chatbot trained on your business</li>
              <li>Custom features (booking, ordering, payments)</li>
              <li>Deep local SEO (schema, GBP, industry-specific)</li>
              <li>You own the code — no lock-in, ever</li>
              <li>Live in 1-3 weeks, not months</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Math -->
  <section class="bg-[#FBF8F4] py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1A1814] text-center mb-8">The math over 3 years</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#E8E4DE]">
              <th class="text-left py-3 font-medium text-[#1A1814]/60">Option</th>
              <th class="text-right py-3 font-medium text-[#1A1814]/60">Year 1</th>
              <th class="text-right py-3 font-medium text-[#1A1814]/60">Year 3</th>
              <th class="text-center py-3 font-medium text-[#1A1814]/60">Own it?</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#E8E4DE]">
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 text-[#1A1814]">Wix Business</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$432</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$1,296</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center text-red-600">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 text-[#1A1814]">Squarespace Plus</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$468</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$1,404</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center text-red-600">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 text-[#1A1814]">B12 Professional</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$2,388</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$7,164</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-600">Partial</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 text-[#1A1814]">Local WordPress Agency</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$5,000+</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right text-[#1A1814]/70">$7,000+</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-600">Sometimes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#B85C38]/5">
              <td class="py-3 font-medium text-[#B85C38]">UWC</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right font-medium text-[#B85C38]">$750-$3,500</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-right font-medium text-[#B85C38]">$750-$3,500</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-600 font-medium">Yes, always</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-[#1A1814]/50 mt-4 text-center">UWC is a one-time cost. No monthly platform fees. Optional retainer for ongoing updates.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Templates Can't Do -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1A1814] text-center mb-8">What you can't get from a template</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#E8E4DE] p-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">AI chatbot trained on your business</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#1A1814]/60 mt-1">Answers questions about your services, menu, pricing, hours — 24/7. No AI builder offers this.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#E8E4DE] p-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Custom business logic</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#1A1814]/60 mt-1">Booking with your rules, commission-free ordering, loyalty programs, membership systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#E8E4DE] p-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">95+ Google PageSpeed</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#1A1814]/60 mt-1">Template builders score 45-70. Faster sites rank higher on Google. We consistently hit 95+.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#E8E4DE] p-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-[#1A1814]">Deep local SEO</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#1A1814]/60 mt-1">Custom schema, Google Business optimization, industry-specific structured data. Not just "SEO tools."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-[#B85C38] py-12 px-6 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Ready to see what custom looks like?</h2>
    <p class="text-white/80 mt-2 max-w-md mx-auto">Tell us about your business. We'll tell you what it costs — before we start.</p>
    <a href="/get-started?utm_source=compare&utm_medium=cta" class="inline-block mt-6 bg-white text-[#B85C38] font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-white/90">
      Tell us about your business
    </a>
  </section>
</PublicLayout>
